pageTitle: Records Set for Coldest High Temperatures Friday and Saturday

textBeforeTable: After the warm weather that occurred on Thursday, temperatures dropped off significantly behind a cold front, and remained that way through the weekend.  While no record lows have been set so far, several records have fallen for coldest high temperature, which have been in the mid 40s to around 50 degrees.  Normal high temperatures for this time of year are in the upper 60s to lower 70s.
